The US legislature should return to the negotiating table as soon as possible and pass the draft financial support bill, according to Australian Prime Minister Kevin Rudd.
Otherwise, other countries could be affected by the break-in.
A bloodbath of American stocks
The US House of Representatives on Monday rejected a plan to support the financial system, which would cost up to $700 billion.
