The vote on this is due to take place early next week.
The American legislature made a breakthrough in talks to pass a $700 billion bailout for the American financial system.
But this is not a victory.
The lawmakers still have to negotiate some details of the agreement before they can publish the final version of the law and vote on it.
The plan to support the financial system will be discussed in the US Congress on Monday.
The Commission has also been asked to submit a proposal for a regulation on the protection of the environment.
