Warsaw exchange offers to buy Prague exchange
The Warsaw Stock Exchange has offered around EUR 200 million, or CZK 5 billion, for the purchase of 100% of the shares of the Prague Stock Exchange.
Ludwik Sobolewski, president of the Warsaw Stock Exchange, confirmed the offer made by the Poles despite the fact that they had previously been excluded by the Czechs as potential owners of their stock exchange.
The reason is that the Warsaw Stock Exchange is wholly state-owned.
